Introduction: The variables of interest are the BsmtFinSF1 and the SalePrice. Our SalePrice variable would be our response variable and out 
predictor variables would be the BsmtFinSF1. Our sample data comes from an original data source, which is the Anna Montoya, DataCanary.
(2016).House Prices - Advanced Regression Techniques. It is from Kaggle and obtained from <https://kaggle.com/competitions/house-prices-advanced-regression-techniques> ([https://kaggle.com/competitions/house-pricesadvanced-regression-techniques](https://kaggle.com/competitions/house-pricesadvanced-regression-techniques){.uri}).
From the sample data, we can know that the population we are inferring our results on are all residential houses in Ames, Iowa.
We will be inferring and analysing our plots from the two variables of interest that we have.
